In the ajax `OnSuccess` you&#39;re not passing the position id for the function `deactivate` thats why your script does nothing because function parameter `data` is null 

```
@Ajax.ActionLink(&quot;1-Click-Apply&quot;, &quot;OneClickApply&quot;, new { id = item.PositionID }, new AjaxOptions
 {
       HttpMethod = &quot;POST&quot;,
       Confirm = &quot;Are you sure you want to apply for &quot; + item.Title + &quot;?&quot;,
       OnSuccess = &quot;deactive&quot;
  }, new { @class = &quot;btn btn-info float-right&quot;, id = &quot;oneClick&quot; + item.PositionID, style = &quot;margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px&quot; })
  }
```

so to correct this you should call `deactive()` with `PositionId` parameter;
```
OnSuccess = &quot;deactive(&#39;&quot; + item.PositionID + &quot;&#39;)&quot;
```

and then in your script you can access the id by doing
```
function deactive(id) {
        $(&#39;#oneClick&#39; + id)addClass(&#39;disabled&#39;).text(&quot;Applied&quot;);

    }
```

Your Ajax Helper should look like this; 
```
@Ajax.ActionLink(&quot;1-Click-Apply&quot;, &quot;OneClickApply&quot;, new { id = item.PositionID }, new AjaxOptions
 {
       HttpMethod = &quot;POST&quot;,
       Confirm = &quot;Are you sure you want to apply for &quot; + item.Title + &quot;?&quot;,
       OnSuccess = &quot;deactive(&#39;&quot; + item.PositionID + &quot;&#39;)&quot;
  }, new { @class = &quot;btn btn-info float-right&quot;, id = &quot;oneClick&quot; + item.PositionID, style = &quot;margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px&quot; })
  }
```

